    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Until the spell ends, wind whirls around you, and you gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li>Ranged attacks made against you have disadvantage on the attack roll.</li><li>Ranged attacks you make are done at advantage.</li><li>You gain a flying speed of 60 feet with hover. If you are still flying when the spell ends, you fall, unless you can somehow prevent it.</li><li>When you take the attack action, you can replace one of your attacks to create a 15-foot cube of swirling wind centered on a point you can see within 60 feet of you. Each creature in that area must make a Constitution saving throw. A creature takes 2d10 bludgeoning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. If a Large or smaller creature fails the save, that creature is also pushed up to 10 feet away from the center of the cube.</li></ul><p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 9th level or higher, the duration granted no longer requires concentration.</p>",
